The paper deals with a game-theoretic model of selfish routing, which falls under the category of algorithmic game theory (cs.GT). The concept of risk-aversion is central to the paper, which suggests that it could also be classified under the sub-category of network economics (cs.NE). The paper also provides bounds on the inefficiency of the system, which could be seen as a machine learning problem, falling under the sub-category of learning (cs.LG). The paper heavily relies on mathematical analysis and graph theory, which suggests that it could also be classified under the sub-categories of data structures and algorithms (cs.DS) and information theory (cs.IT).
